Q1. Find the sum of first ‘N’ odd numbers.
    n=5                sum=25
    n=2                sum=4

Q2. Create a VI to animate a horse running. Use the picture ring control to insert and display
pictures to be animated.
    Horse animation process is executing in a continuous loop.

Q3. Create a program for finding the factorial of a number and use this as subVI to compute NPr
and NCr.
    N=5                NPr=120
    r=4                NCr=5

    N=6                NPr=720
    r=4                NCr=15

Q4. Compute the sum of digits of a given integer using for loop.
    #3 Digit numbers
    n=100              sum=1
    n=575              sum=17

Q5. Find the sum of values lying between ‘P’ and ‘Q’. Where ‘P’ and ‘Q’ are positive integers
and P>Q.
    P=5                sum=7
    Q=2
    P=7                sum=11
    Q=4